Description: Taxonomic resolution of length to weight parameters; genus means values are an average of multiple species in a genus while congener means that values are from a single species in the same genus. Enumeration_xml: Body ShapeWhen no formula parameters are available at Family level, parameters were determined by body shape per Kulbicki method.ConfamilyParameters were taken from another member of the same family.CongenerParameters were taken from another member of the same genus.ConorderParameters were taken from another member of the same order.FamilyParameters are based on a family average.GenusParameters are based on a genus average.SpeciesParameters are specific to this species.

Description: Source of total length to fork length parameter; photograph means that I estimated Lb from a photograph of a single individual (photographs were obtained from Fish Base), genus average and family average mean that I took an average of the other fish in the same genus or family from our species list. Lb was assumed to be 1 for some unidentified species for which I had "No Info." Also several species (mainly from the families Labridae and Scaridae) had TL to FL relationships that vary with size (i.e., large Terminal Phase individuals have slightly forked tails). For these species I set Lb = 1 which would overestimate the FL of TP individuals.
